  <div class="timeline">
    <div class="timeline__item">
      <div class="timeline__period">2009 to 2013</div>
      <h3 class="timeline__role">Product Manager, Blackboard</h3>
      <p>Started my career proving that UX was a revenue lever, not a cost center. Shipped 84 mobile
      apps, drove a 64% year-over-year jump in sales through design improvements, and helped build the
      case that contributed to the company's eventual acquisition.</p>
    </div>
    <div class="timeline__item">
      <div class="timeline__period">2012 to 2017</div>
      <h3 class="timeline__role">PhD Researcher, Virginia Tech, alongside IBM and Amazon/Sonos</h3>
      <p>Pursued a PhD in Industrial &amp; Systems Engineering while working full industry roles in
      parallel: product management at IBM scaling SaaS adoption 75x, then concurrent UX research for
      Amazon Echo and Sonos Play:5. Selected as an NSF I-Corps Graduate Fellow.</p>
    </div>
    <div class="timeline__item">
      <div class="timeline__period">2014 to 2017</div>
      <h3 class="timeline__role">Senior Product Manager, Joint Special Operations Command</h3>
      <p>A fourth concurrent thread during the PhD years: product strategy for UX and mobile innovation
      inside a defense command. Secured $750K in research funding by building the business case from
      scratch, then shipped two prototypes on time and under budget.</p>
    </div>
    <div class="timeline__item">
      <div class="timeline__period">2018 to 2020</div>
      <h3 class="timeline__role">Lab Director &amp; Visiting Professor, Brigham Young University</h3>
      <p>Founded a university innovation lab from zero, raised $325K, and mentored 200+ students through
      real AR/VR and mobile product delivery, while teaching across Mixed Reality, HCI, and UX.</p>
    </div>
    <div class="timeline__item">
      <div class="timeline__period">2018 to 2026</div>
      <h3 class="timeline__role">Senior Technical Product Manager to Principal AI Product Strategist, BluePath Labs</h3>
      <p>Eight years at a defense technology contractor. Directed a $45M portfolio across six government
      contracts, authored proposals representing $51B in potential contract value, led AI/LLM research at
      the Army Cybersecurity Institute, and scaled a team from 4 to 12 while doubling contract value.</p>
    </div>
    <div class="timeline__item">
      <div class="timeline__period">2026 to Present</div>
      <h3 class="timeline__role">Senior Technology Solutions Strategist, Large Public Institution</h3>
      <p>Scaling from 1 to 4 concurrent AI programs and architecting the institutional platform spec that
      unifies them, from vendor evaluation through architecture-lock.</p>
    </div>
  </div>
</section>

<section class="section section--border-top wrap">
  <h2 class="section-label">How I Work</h2>
  <div class="card-grid">
    <div class="card">
      <h3>Bridge, don't translate</h3>
      <p class="small">I don't translate between engineering and the business, I sit in both rooms
      well enough that translation isn't necessary.</p>
    </div>
    <div class="card">
      <h3>Governance as infrastructure</h3>
      <p class="small">Compliance and ethics review built into the pipeline from day one ships faster
      than bolting it on after legal finds the problem.</p>
    </div>
    <div class="card">
      <h3>Numbers over opinions</h3>
      <p class="small">If a decision can be modeled, it should be. Multi-criteria frameworks beat
      whoever presents last in the room.</p>
    </div>
  </div>
